          <actionDate>2015-06-03</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Regulatory Predictability for Business Growth Act of 2015</strong></p> <p>This bill adds the definitions of "longstanding interpretative rule" and "revise" to the Administrative Procedure Act (APA). A longstanding interpretative rule is distinguished from an "interpretative rule" if it has been in effect for at least one&nbsp;year. If a rule is a longstanding interpretative rule, it remains subject to the general notice of proposed rulemaking and comment and publication provisions of the APA. </p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-10-29T20:59:56Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
